# Hive & Secure Storage Conventions

## Credentials Must Use flutter_secure_storage

API tokens and passwords must **only** ever be stored in `flutter_secure_storage`,
which is backed by the Android Keystore. This is a hard security requirement.

**Never** store credentials (API tokens, passwords, session tickets) in:
- `hive_ce` boxes
- `SharedPreferences`
- Any file-based storage

Credentials are stored keyed by server ID and loaded at runtime when
constructing `ProxmoxApiClient`.

## Server Freezed Model: No Credential Fields

The `Server` Freezed model must not include credential fields. It stores only
non-sensitive metadata:

```dart
@freezed
class Server with _$Server {
  const factory Server({
    required String id,
    required String name,
    required String host,
    required int port,
    required ServerAuthType authType,
    required bool allowSelfSigned,
  }) = _Server;
  // No apiToken field. No password field. Credentials live in flutter_secure_storage.
}
```

## Storage Separation at a Glance

| Data | Storage |
|---|---|
| Server name, host, port, authType, allowSelfSigned | `hive_ce` |
| API token, username/password | `flutter_secure_storage` (keyed by server ID) |
| Active session ticket + CSRF token (username/password auth) | In-memory only — never persisted |
| User preferences (theme) | `hive_ce` |

## Loading Credentials at Runtime

Credentials are fetched from `flutter_secure_storage` by server ID when
building the `ProxmoxApiClient`. They are never stored on the `Server` object
after loading.

```dart
final token = await _secureStorage.read(key: 'apiToken_${server.id}');
final client = ProxmoxApiClient(server: server, apiToken: token);
// token is not written back to the Server model
```
